The course gives a contemporary overview of the psychology of personality and individual differences. Main topics: measurement and classification of personality traits and mental abilities; personality, situations and behaviour; psychobiology and behavioural genetics of personality and intelligence; cognitive psychology of personality; self-regulation; personality development; culture and personality; self-concept; metatheory of personality.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to give an overview of main research issues and methods in contemporary psychology of  personality and individual differences, and an introduction to its history and possibilities of theoretical integration.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student knows the main research directions and methods of contemporary psychology of personality and individual differences and is able to critically analyze them (incl. reading an empirical research paper and to reason about the conclusions and results).
